In [27]:
# Aggregate the number of bird strikes by year
bird_strikes_by_year = df.groupby(df['FlightDate'].dt.year).size()

#line plot to visualize the number of bird strikes over the years
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(bird_strikes_by_year.index, bird_strikes_by_year.values, marker='o', linestyle='-')
plt.title('Bird Strikes Over the Years in US')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

#Group data by effect of bird strikes and impact on flight
effect_impact_group = df.groupby(['Effect: Impact to flight', 'Effect: Indicated Damage'])

#  Effect of bird strikes and impact on flight
effect_impact_count = effect_impact_group.size().unstack(fill_value=0)
effect_impact_count.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title('Effect of Bird Strikes & Impact on Flight')
plt.xlabel('Effect: Impact to Flight')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(title='Effect: Indicated Damage')
